<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-06-07T09:45:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-06-07T09:45:00-05:00" n="440" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d440">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/3081: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-06-07T09:00:00-05:45"><hi rend="italic">June 7,
                                        1924—9 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 8:30
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>108. During interview with President last evening I informed him of the
                            contents of your 66, June 5, 5 p.m. He said he would withdraw his
                            candidacy …</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>